#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:1
msgid "Semantic Analysis"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:3
msgid ""
"Different government agencies publish DMN decision models using their own "
"naming conventions for variables. When one agency's output variable and "
"another agency's input variable represent the same concept but have "
"different identifiers, exact identifier matching fails and chain building "
"appears to break. The Semantic Analysis feature resolves this by using SKOS "
"concept mappings to discover variable relationships across agency boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:12
msgid "The problem"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:14
msgid ""
"SVB output:   \"aanvragerIs181920\"\n"
"SZW input:    \"aanvragerIs181920\"   ← exact match, chain works\n"
"\n"
"Zorg output:  \"heeftJuisteLeeftijd\"\n"
"Belasting input: \"leeftijd_requirement\"  ← no exact match, chain appears "
"broken"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:24
msgid "The solution"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:26
msgid ""
"The CPSV Editor, when publishing a DMN to TriplyDB, generates a "
"`skos:Concept` for each input and output variable. When two variables from "
"different agencies represent the same thing, both concepts carry a "
"`skos:exactMatch` link pointing to the same shared concept URI from a "
"central vocabulary. The Linked Data Explorer queries for these shared "
"concept URIs and surfaces all variable pairs that connect via them."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:28
msgid ""
"This means a chain between Zorg and Belasting is discoverable and executable "
"— not as a DRD (because the identifiers differ), but as a sequential chain "
"where the backend maps the output value of one step to the correctly named "
"input of the next."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:32
msgid "Semantic Analysis tab"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:34
msgid ""
"In the Chain Builder, the **Semantic Analysis** tab (next to the chain "
"composer) shows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:36
msgid ""
"**Statistics** — counts of semantic equivalences, semantic chain "
"suggestions, and exact match links in the current endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:37
msgid ""
"**Semantic Equivalences** — a table of variable pairs sharing a concept, "
"with labels, notations, and the shared concept URI"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:38
msgid ""
"**Semantic Chain Suggestions** — output/input pairs from different DMNs that "
"are connectable via a shared concept but would not appear in exact-match "
"chain detection"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:40
msgid ""
"Results populate automatically from the active TriplyDB endpoint whenever NL-"
"SBB concepts with `skos:exactMatch` links have been published from the CPSV "
"Editor."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:44
msgid "Standards"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:46
msgid "The semantic matching system follows these specifications:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:48
msgid ""
"**NL-SBB** — Dutch profile for SKOS concept schemes, used for the concept "
"vocabulary"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:49
msgid ""
"**SKOS** (`skos:exactMatch`) — cross-vocabulary alignment between agency-"
"specific variable concepts and the shared central vocabulary"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:50
msgid ""
"**CPSV-AP 3.2.0** (`cpsv:Input`, `cpsv:Output`) — linked to concepts via "
"`dct:subject`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:54
msgid "Graph view"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Csemantic-analysis.md:56
msgid ""
"In the SPARQL graph visualisation, semantic links (`skos:exactMatch`, "
"`dct:subject`) are rendered as dashed green lines (2.5 px), visually "
"distinct from standard RDF property edges (solid grey, 1.5 px)."
msgstr ""
